Pre-Game Insights: Avram Grant says Zambia holds no fear of Morocco ahead of their 2023 Africa Cup of Nations Group F match.
Morocco coach Walid Regragui emphasizes the difficulty of the tournament both physically and mentally.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zambia are third on the group standings on two points and will need a positive result to advance into the knockout rounds.
Morocco followed their Afcon opening 3-0 win over Tanzania with a 1-1 draw against DR Congo.
Others: Zambia will be without defender Roderick Kabwe due to suspension, while Kelvin Kapumbu could lose his starting spot after an indifferent showing against Tanzania.
Morocco have no reported injury issues but could shuffle up their line-up with the likes of Ayoub El Kaabi or Azzedine Ounahi.
